Yobe State Governor, Mai Mala Buni, has congratulated Prof. Ibrahim Gambari on his appointment as the new Chief of Staff to President Muhammadu Buhari. Governor Buni in a statement he personally signed and made available to newsmen on Wednesday, described Prof. Gambari as a seasoned diplomat and renowned scholar who has had a prosperous carrier in diplomacy, noting that the academic has no doubt done Nigeria proud at different capacities locally and internationally. “The government and people of Yobe State congratulate Prof. Ibrahim Gambari CFR on his appointment as the new Chief of Staff to His Excellency President Muhammadu Buhari GCFR. “Prof. Gambari, a seasoned diplomat and renowned scholar who has had a prosperous career in diplomacy and the academics, has no doubt done Nigeria proud at different times in various capacities locally and internationally,” Buni said. As Chief of staff to the President, the governor expressed confident that Gambari will bring his wealth of experience to bear to add value to the government of President Muhammadu Buhari. “It is our prayer that Allah grant you the wisdom, strength and good health to execute your duties successfully to the benefit of Nigerians. “I also wish to congratulate Mr. President for appointing a very competent hand into the office of the Chief of Staff to support him in the task of serving Nigeria diligently. “On behalf of my humble self, government and the good people of Yobe state, l wish you a successful tenure of office,” Buni prayed. Gambari: Ekweremadu, Obaseki reveals what Buhari’s Chief of Staff will offer Nigeria Gambari: Tinubu speaks on Buhari's choice of new Chief of Staff Why Nigerians should accept Ibrahim Gambari’s appointment - Sanwo-Olu